            <p>The collection is organized into the following series: I. Biographical files; II.
                Correspondence, 1848-1964; III. Postcards, 1907-1919; IV. Diaries, 1925-1977; V.
                Subject files arranged alphabetically by heading; and VI. Photographs. </p>
        </arrangement>

        <!-- required for collection level; optional for lower levels -->
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">

            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The Burnham mss., 1848-1977, consist of the papers of Indiana University
                administrator, Walter Erastus Burnham, 1905-1980, and of his parents, grandparents
                and other family members. The collection includes Burnham's correspondence,
                particularly letters received from his mother, Ida May (Corson) Burnham (1875-1962);
                Walter Burnham's diaries from 1936-1975; his military papers; writings by him;
                memorabilia of his grandmother, Carrie A. (Pease) Burnham (1837-1921), including a
                Composition Book with temperance songs, rhymes, list of books read, etc.;
                photographs of family and friends, the boys schools, etc.; and a group of fifty or
                more postcards, 1907-1919, addressed chiefly to Burnham's parents when they lived in
                Bellevue, Kentucky.</p>
        </scopecontent>

